dslRule:
@id: string.invert-equals.null-safe.equals
@description: Invert Object.equals() call to make it null-safe, when receiver is nullable and argument is non-nullable.
Beware: this changes behavior from NullPointerException to false/true if receiver is null.
Requires a non-nullable argument to become the new receiver.
@severity: info
$var1.equals($var2)
:: isNullable($var1, 5) && isNonNull($var2)
=> $var2.equals($var1)
;;

@id: string.invert-equals.null-safe.equalsignorecase
@description: Invert String.equalsIgnoreCase() call to make it null-safe, when receiver is nullable and argument is non-nullable.
Beware: this changes behavior from NullPointerException to false/true if receiver is null.
Requires a non-nullable argument to become the new receiver.
@severity: info
$var1.equalsIgnoreCase($var2)
:: isNullable($var1, 5) && isNonNull($var2)
=> $var2.equalsIgnoreCase($var1)
;;

